		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Makes me wonder about Brick Game too (though I don't have one at hand), although that one is a lot more annoying in that games didn't come in separate cartridges so there are a ton of models that just happen to have different games and with tons of minor variations over time. The hardware seems pretty neat though as far as working properly goes, and they even implemented a suspend feature before any of the major handhelds did (power off while paused, the game will be restored on power on)

		

